## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="33881-102">Eine Instanz von <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> wird erstellt, wenn die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> -Objekt löst die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> Ereignis.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object raises the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="33881-103">Um Informationen über das Ergebnis der Erkennung zu erhalten, Zugriff auf die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> Eigenschaft im Handler für das Ereignis.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-103">To obtain information about the result of recognition, access the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property in the handler for the event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="33881-104">Emulation versteht man das nach dem Text, anstelle von Audio, die Eingabe für eine Spracherkennungsmoduls ist.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-104">Emulation is the process by which text, instead of audio, is the input to a speech recognition engine.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="33881-105">Umgehen der Audioeingänge für eine <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> Objekts während der Emulation, verwenden die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> Methode.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-105">To bypass the audio inputs for a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object during emulation, use the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SetInputToNull%2A> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="33881-106">Wenn die Spracherkennungsmoduls beim Auftreten einer Ausnahme während der Erkennungsvorgang der <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> Eigenschaftensatz auf die Ausnahme und die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> -Eigenschaftensatz auf `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-106">If the speech recognition engine encounters an exception during the recognition operation, the <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs.Error%2A> property is set to the exception and the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property is set to `null`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="33881-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> wird von <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs> abgeleitet.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.ComponentModel.AsyncCompletedEventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="33881-108">Das folgende Beispiel fügt einen Ereignishandler für das <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> Ereignis, um eine <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-108">The following example adds an event handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.EmulateRecognizeCompleted> event to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="33881-109">Der Handler Ruft den erkannten Text aus der <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> Eigenschaft.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="33881-109">The handler gets the recognized text from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs.Result%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the speech recognition engine.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.  
  sre.EmulateRecognizeCompleted += new EventHandler<EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs>(sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Handle the EmulateRecognizeCompleted event.   
void sre_EmulateRecognizeCompleted(object sender, EmulateRecognizeCompletedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  string phrase = e.Result.Text;  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
}  
  
```
